				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just another gear &quot;help me&quot; question<a name="70511"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 1 04 2:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As far as soloing with charm at 39, I recommend 3 things.
<br />

<br />
1)  A good wind instrument.  Need this to invis to break charm.  Also, the better the wind mod, the longer charm will average, as wind is the determining factor on how much MR is lowered on the charm.  Bloodstained flute is not bad.  Alternately you can get tiny cloak of darkest night if you have the capability for an even better invis.
<br />

<br />
2)  FT.  This can be acquired by items or tribute.  If you try to charm mobs close to your level your mana will run out quickly, they just break too much.  You have to have at least FT5 to maintain mana assuming every charm lasts FULL duration. (FT5 + 1 natural regen = 60 standing mana regen per minute which is how long a charm lasts at MAX duration).  Even at FT5 you will still lose mana over time as duration will not always max.  By level 55 I had composers boots, EoTS, and Spiritmaster war beads, because I hate not &quot;owning&quot; my FT like with tribute.  I value these items over any hp gear I have, and will value them even more when I get fade.
<br />

<br />
3)  I also recommend a decent percussion instrument.  Battle drummers main gauche does the job and it can be equipped simultaneously with your flute.  This will help with selos, and with chanting down former pets.  You do not want to allow pets to do all the damage.  If a former pet breaks, and you finish it off yourself, you get 100% of the experience.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
