				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Just another gear &amp;quot;help me&amp;quot; question<a name="70575"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 3 04 10:16 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Okay, so which slot should I look to fill with FT items.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Earring of the solstice would be cheapest (FT1), Spiritmaster war beads (neck - FT2) if you have the money.  Boots of flowing slime (FT3) not wearable till 51, composer's boots (FT3) not wearable till 55.  Lots of FT options from ldon later on.  Almost all other tradables have horrendous stats for the amount of FT they provide. 
<br />

<br />
Blessed coldain prayer shawl (FT3) is the only other decent piece I can think of that a &quot;casual&quot; player can do, but you need time and money for the tradeskills, and friends for the last part (1 group 65+).
<br />

<br />
Now, if you're willing to do some raiding, your options open dramatically.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
